<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/2031</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-14"><hi rend="italic">June 14,
                                        1919</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 294</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has had under
                                consideration the request made by the Military Governor of the
                                Dominican Republic to transfer to the Military Government the
                                collection of the internal revenues of the Republic.</p>
                            <pb facs="0240" n="155" xml:id="pg_155"/>
                            <p>After careful consideration of the subject, the Department has
                                reached the conclusion that it cannot approve the proposed transfer,
                                and you will so inform the Military Governor.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L.
                                Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>